Subject: [PATCH 135/139] dt-bindings: display: sunxi: sun8i-dw-hdmi: add
 ddc-en gpio

Some boards have a GPIO that controls the level shifting transistor of
HDMI DDC pins.

Add a ddc-en-gpios property to sun8i-dw-hdmi , which refer to such GPIOs.

Signed-off-by: Icenowy Zheng <icenowy@aosc.io>
---
 Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
index d91c18548694..e5e5427e60f3 100644
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
@@ -119,6 +119,9 @@ Required properties:
   - resets: phandle to the reset controller driving the PHY
   - reset-names: must be "phy"
 
+Optional properties:
+  - ddc-en-gpios: gate GPIOs for the HDMI DDC pins
+
 H3 and A64 HDMI PHY require additional clocks:
   - pll-0: parent of phy clock
   - pll-1: second possible phy clock parent (A64 only)
